---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'May 2025';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Amplifly's privacy policy. Everything you log lives on your device by default. No analytics, no advertising, no data sales."
>
  <main class="container mx-auto px-6 pt-32 pb-20 max-w-3xl">

    <h1 class="text-deep-navy text-4xl font-bold mb-3">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-neutral-gray text-sm mb-12">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-10 text-accessible-gray">

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-deep-navy text-2xl font-bold mb-4">The short version</h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed">
          Everything you do in Amplifly — brain check-ins, flow sessions, your ND profile,
          the recommendation model — lives on your device in local storage. We don't collect
          analytics, crash reports, or advertising data. A free optional account lets you
          sync your data across devices. That sync data is stored on Supabase's secure servers,
          encrypted in transit, and is never sold, shared, or used for any purpose other than
          restoring your data.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-deep-navy text-2xl font-bold mb-4">What data Amplifly stores</h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4">If you use Amplifly without an account, the following is stored <strong>only on your device</strong> using AsyncStorage:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-base">
          <li>Daily brain check-ins (brain state + optional note + timestamp)</li>
          <li>Flow sessions (activity, duration, intensity, interest level, helpers, drains, optional note)</li>
          <li>Your ND profile (which profiles you selected, executive function rating, working memory rating)</li>
          <li>Your name (optional, used only for personalized greetings)</li>
          <li>The recommendation engine's learned state (Beta posteriors per condition/context cell)</li>
          <li>The personal calibration layer for the flow forecast</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mt-4">None of this leaves your device unless you create an account.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-deep-navy text-2xl font-bold mb-4">If you create an account</h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Creating an account is free and optional. Its only purpose is to let you restore your
          data on a new device. When you sign in:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-base">
          <li>Your email address is stored by Supabase for authentication.</li>
          <li>Your brain checks, flow sessions, user profile, and bandit state are synced to Supabase's servers and stored encrypted at rest.</li>
          <li>Sync happens automatically in the background. Signing out immediately stops syncing. Your local data remains on your device.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mt-4">
          Supabase is an open-source database platform. Their infrastructure is hosted on AWS.
          You can read Supabase's privacy and security documentation at{' '}
          <a href="https://supabase.com/privacy" class="text-bright-blue hover:underline">supabase.com/privacy</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-deep-navy text-2xl font-bold mb-4">What we do not collect</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-base">
          <li>No analytics (no Mixpanel, Amplitude, or similar)</li>
          <li>No crash reporting (no Sentry, Bugsnag, or similar)</li>
          <li>No advertising identifiers (no IDFA, GAID)</li>
          <li>No usage telemetry of any kind</li>
          <li>No data is ever sold, shared with advertisers, or used for any purpose other than the functionality described above</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-deep-navy text-2xl font-bold mb-4">The recommendation engine and flow forecast</h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed">
          The recommendation engine is a Thompson-sampling contextual bandit. All computation
          runs on your device. If you have an account, the model's learned posteriors sync to
          Supabase so your preferences carry across devices — but nothing is used for advertising
          or shared with anyone.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mt-4">
          The flow forecast uses a small neural network trained on synthetic data built from
          published research on focus and neurodivergence. The weights are fixed and ship with
          the app. Only a personal calibration layer updates as you log sessions, and that stays
          on your device (or syncs to your account if you have one).
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-deep-navy text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Deleting your data</h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed">
          To delete your account and all data stored in Supabase, email us at{' '}
          <a href="mailto:hello@amplifly.app?subject=Delete my account" class="text-bright-blue hover:underline">
            hello@amplifly.app
          </a>{' '}
          with the subject "Delete my account." We will remove all rows associated with your
          user ID and delete your Supabase auth account within 7 days.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mt-4">
          To delete data stored locally on your device, uninstall the app. All AsyncStorage
          data is removed automatically when the app is uninstalled.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-deep-navy text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Children</h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed">
          Amplifly is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal
          information from children under 13.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-deep-navy text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed">
          If we make material changes to this policy, we will update the date at the top of
          this page and notify users via in-app messaging where possible.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-deep-navy text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Contact</h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed">
          Questions about privacy? Email{' '}
          <a href="mailto:hello@amplifly.app" class="text-bright-blue hover:underline">hello@amplifly.app</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
